element.name: The Black Rose by Shakes, Virtual Cache (1/1)
element.description: A VIRTUAL cache to be found on the Howth peninsula
element.long-description: I don't want to give anything away about the cache. Let's just say that it has musical connections. There are a number of entrances but the one at N53 22.801 W006 05.614 will be the nearest and most direct. Take a photo of yourself and/or a GPS reading and send it to me (see my profile for email address) for confirmation. PLEASE do not post a photo with your log - thanks. While you're in Howth why not take a trip up to the "summit" at N53 22.243 W006 03.290 and take a look across Dublin Bay and if you are really up for it then "do" the cliff walk all the way into Howth itself. If you're not into exercise then enjoy a pint in the pub at the bottom of the hill!

Got the go ahead from Shakes to log it after visiting the cache on Sunday. Thanks for bringing us here !

I had a fair idea of what the cache was about, sure enough I was right. Nice to be here though. Took a pic, will send on. TFTC, Spark_ie

2010-04-05T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
Once I realised what this cache was, I simply had to do it. My one and only encounter with the 'Black Rose' took place in 1976, about 200 yards from the location of this cache.
TFTC

Did not know what to expect here but it was a pleasant surprise! Thanks for a great cache!

This cache was not what I expected but I'm happy to have been here. T4TC
